    "abstractNote": "This is a study and edition of Bcom Idan ral gri's \"Bstan pa rgyas pa rgyan gyi nyi 'od\". Probably composed in the last decades of the 13th century, this systematic list of Buddhist Sutras, Tantras, Shastras, and related genres translated primarily from Sanskrit languages, holds an important place in the history of Buddhist literature in Tibet.",
